text.title: Sydfynske Øhav
text.summary: Sydfynske Øhav, an Archipelago of 55 islands connected by ferries and bridges south of the Danish island of Funen with over 20,000 inhabitants, is a scenic tourist destination with rare species such as Arctic Tern birds, Shore Crabs, Beach Otters and Seals and a 220 km hiking trail, reachable by boat, highway or train.
